FT  03 OCT 94 / The Labour Party in Blackpool: Quotas for women to be upheld
Labour will this week reaffirm its policy on quotas for women in spite of
growing opposition.
However, a statement from the national executive committee yesterday said
the policy should be interpreted flexibly and with sensitivity. Where there
are disputes at local level the issue will be go to the NEC.
Observer, Page 19
